                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d91">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/3410: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-30T14:00:00+07:00"
                            >August 30, 1943—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 1—4:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1595. During conversation which the British Ambassador and I had with Chiang
                    Kai-shek August 29, Chiang stated that he welcomed Mountbatten’s<note n="27"
                        xml:id="d91fn27">Vice Admiral Lord Louis Mountbatten, appointed Supreme
                        Allied Commander, Southeast Asia.</note> appointment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
